formatted_address: 3 Yuan Ching Rd, #01-01 SuperBowl Jurong, Singapore 618642
name: Kampong House Mini Wok

reviews.text:
The sight of sliced fish served in an old-school aluminium steamboat pot is too tempting to resist.
The soup is savoury with lots of won bok [a.k.a. Chinese cabbage], tomatoes and tofu. However, the fried fish slices are mostly batter with just a morsel of fish meat within.
On the other hand, the prawn paste chicken [a.k.a. har cheong gai] is a must try here. We love the crispy golden-brown skin with juicy meat and the fermented shrimp ü¶ê paste is strong!
